  "prompt": "Are there other movies like The Secret?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several movies and documentaries similar to \"The Secret\" that explore themes like the law of attraction, positive thinking, and personal development. Here are a few:\n\n1. **What the Bleep Do We Know!? (2004)** - This film blends scientific theories with spiritual concepts, exploring the idea that consciousness and thoughts influence the physical world.\n\n2. **The Moses Code (2008)** - This documentary explores spiritual ideas about manifesting abundance and living a purposeful life, building on concepts introduced in \"The Secret.\"\n\n3. **The Power of Intention (2008)** - Based on Dr. Wayne Dyer's teachings, this film delves into the impact of intention on life's outcomes and personal development.\n\n4. **You Can Heal Your Life (2007)** - Based on Louise Hay's book, this film discusses the power of affirmations and positive thinking in overcoming personal challenges and improving health.\n\n5. **Awake: The Life of Yogananda (2014)** - This documentary chronicles the life of Paramahansa Yogananda, exploring his teachings on self-realization and inner peace.\n\n6. **The Shift (2009)** - Another film featuring Dr. Wayne Dyer, it explores the shift from ambition to meaning as a path to true fulfillment and personal growth.\n\n7. **Heal (2017)** - This documentary examines the science and spirituality behind the body\u2019s ability to heal itself, focusing on the mind-body connection.\n\nThese films provide insights into similar themes of self-improvement, spirituality, and the potential power of thoughts and beliefs in shaping one's reality.",
